CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 3, 1965, pg. 4, reads: "'Home Sweet Home' - This primitive accommodation, jammed with discarded pieces, may seem like an abandoned 'wreck' to the more fortunate among us. Actually, it is merely the room next door for the man seen entering living quarter by way of a glass-bare door.  This kind of eyesore is being wiped out on the Hill, by Safety director Craig, in response to complaints by aroused businessmen. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: View through window into dilapidated interior with sink, toilet, and overturned refrigerator, and man wearing cap, seen through door in background
